The paper deals with the problem of generalized zero-shot learning, which involves both computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. The paper proposes a new method for GZSL based on multi-modal training and testing processes, which involves the use of visual and semantic classifiers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the CV (cs.CV) and ML (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of Bayesian inference, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also deals with multi-modal learning, which is a topic that falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
